{"name":"PDC - Kess-Hashari","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"shipfeatures","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 125\">\n<p><strong>Kesh-Hashari Point Defense Cannons</strong></p>\n<p>A type of PDC manufactured by Kess-Hashari. The Outer Planets Alliance's retrofitted OPAS Behemoth is equipped with a total of 170 of these weapons to compensate for its large target profile and poor maneuverability.</p>\n<p>A point defense cannon (PDC) is a rapid-fire projectile weapon used by all military-grade spaceships for defense against missiles and ships.</p>\n<p>PDCs are turreted rotary autocannons, utilizing a set of more, or less than, six spinning barrels to spew out thousands of rounds per minute to intercept incoming ordnance. PDCs are laid out on a ship's hull to cover all angles with overlapping fields of fire, providing a \"curtain of steel\" to more easily and effectively take out missiles. They also utilize thrusters on their rear to counteract the recoil of the firing cannon that would otherwise knock the ship off course. Some turrets can also be retracted into the hull and can extend outwards in mere seconds.</p>\n<p>PDCs are computer-controlled as even juiced-up human gunners would find it nearly impossible to effectively track and destroy fast targets like torpedoes. Human gunners do, however, select targets for their guns. PDCs are mainly used against guided ordinance, but they also perform fairly well as close range ship-to-ship weapons and can be used for direct space-to-surface strikes on personnel. The rounds seem able to penetrate the armor on most smaller ships.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":0,"quantity":1,"equiped":false,"dmgType":"stun","dmgSource":"impact","nrDice":"1","diceType":"6","extraValue":0,"dmgAbl":"str","type":"weapon","damage":"2d6","sensorMod":0,"maneuverSizeStep":0,"juiceMod":0,"hullPlating":0,"hullMod":0,"useFocus":"","useAbl":"","quality":"quality","isActive":true},"flags":{},"img":"systems/age-system/resources/imgs/item-icon/processor.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fz0GdvXvvW8WkbQj"}
{"name":"Torpedo Tube - Heavy","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"shipfeatures","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 125\">\n<p><strong>Configurable Heavy-Grade Torpedo Launcher</strong></p>\n<p>Able to launch up to heavy grade torpedos (6d6 Conventional HE or 5d6 Plasma or Flechette)</p>\n<p>A missile is a powerful self-propelled weapon with an explosive warhead designed to detonate either on contact with its target or in proximity to it. Missiles are the standard primary armament on all warships.</p>\n<p>They are also referred to as \"torpedoes\" when used in ship-to-ship combat, or \"nukes\" when equipped with a nuclear warhead.</p>\n<p>Missiles are long-range, guided missile delivery systems that can be fitted with conventional explosives, plasma warheads (which melt armor and damage systems), flechette warheads (which penetrate ship armor better than an HE warhead, but not as well as a plasma warhead, and don more widespead systemic damage) or varying-yield nuclear warheads. They are jettisoned from the launcher, align themselves with the target, and then begin accelerating to high speed. They can accelerate far faster than a ship, are impossible to dodge, and cause devastating damage to a ship on contact, often wiping out smaller ships with a single hit.</p>\n<p>Their ability to maneuver grants them a much higher effective range than railguns. However, missiles do have a minimum range, so they are usually launched first in an engagement. Missiles are also vulnerable to point defense cannons (PDCs), which can intercept them before closing to effective range. This is countered by firing them in numbers to overwhelm the PDCs on an enemy ship.</p>\n<p>As is seen with the Canterbury's destruction, missiles can have the side-effect of turning the \"splashed\" ship into a destructive field of moving debris, posing a further threat to any other ship in the immediate area. For this reason, the use of missiles in CQB is avoided.</p>\n<p>Being the standard armament on combat vessels, even ships small enough to not be fitted with rail guns can carry missiles. Frigates, corvettes, and patrol boats have one or two firing tubes. Larger ships like cruisers, battleships, and dreadnoughts carry between 3 and 10 tubes.</p>\n<p>Torpedoes follow the direction of shipboard targeting lasers used to &ldquo;paint&rdquo; an enemy, switching over to their own internal guidance systems when necessary. A primary function of point defense cannons is to shoot down incoming torpedoes before they can reach the ship, with electronic warfare countermeasures looking to confuse and throw off their guidance systems so a capable pilot can evade them.</p>\n<p>The ship must be at least Medium-sized to mount a single torpedo launcher. Each additional Size category doubles the capacity for torpedo launchers (two at Large, four at Huge, and so on).</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":0,"quantity":1,"equiped":false,"dmgType":"stun","dmgSource":"impact","nrDice":"1","diceType":"6","extraValue":0,"dmgAbl":"str","type":"weapon","damage":"6d6","sensorMod":0,"maneuverSizeStep":0,"juiceMod":0,"hullPlating":0,"hullMod":0,"useFocus":"","useAbl":"","quality":"quality","isActive":true},"flags":{},"img":"systems/age-system/resources/imgs/item-icon/processor.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pY7Scy9pHpDSDK2i"}
{"name":"PDC - Mikazuki Munitions","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"shipfeatures","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 125\">\n<p><strong>Mikazuki Munitions Point Defense Cannons</strong></p>\n<p>A type of PDC manufactured by Mikazuki Munitions that is used by some older UNN warships. The Leonidas-class battleship is equipped with a staggering 25 Mikazuki Munitions PDCs spread across the surface of its hull for maximum defensive coverage to compensate for their reduced accuracy as a result of the warship's low quality targeting suites. These are not able to be retracted into its utilized vessels hull.</p>\n<p>A point defense cannon (PDC) is a rapid-fire projectile weapon used by all military-grade spaceships for defense against missiles and ships.</p>\n<p>PDCs are turreted rotary autocannons, utilizing a set of more, or less than, six spinning barrels to spew out thousands of rounds per minute to intercept incoming ordnance. PDCs are laid out on a ship's hull to cover all angles with overlapping fields of fire, providing a \"curtain of steel\" to more easily and effectively take out missiles. They also utilize thrusters on their rear to counteract the recoil of the firing cannon that would otherwise knock the ship off course. Some turrets can also be retracted into the hull and can extend outwards in mere seconds.</p>\n<p>PDCs are computer-controlled as even juiced-up human gunners would find it nearly impossible to effectively track and destroy fast targets like torpedoes. Human gunners do, however, select targets for their guns. PDCs are mainly used against guided ordinance, but they also perform fairly well as close range ship-to-ship weapons and can be used for direct space-to-surface strikes on personnel. The rounds seem able to penetrate the armor on most smaller ships.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":0,"quantity":1,"equiped":false,"dmgType":"stun","dmgSource":"impact","nrDice":"1","diceType":"6","extraValue":0,"dmgAbl":"str","type":"weapon","damage":"2d6","sensorMod":0,"maneuverSizeStep":0,"juiceMod":0,"hullPlating":0,"hullMod":0,"useFocus":"","useAbl":"","quality":"quality","isActive":true},"flags":{},"img":"systems/age-system/resources/imgs/item-icon/processor.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rsLQZQtGXuYQiIRJ"}
